Terfa Tilley-Gyado, president of the Atlantic Hall alumni association, has charged members of the association to invest in quality relationships. Tilley-Gyado spoke at the first-ever induction and handover ceremony of the alumni association of the Atlantic Hall School. He said building on such quality relationships will promote an environment where members can share ideas, discuss opportunities, and create a network to manifest their full potentials. The event, which held on November 6 at the Seattle Residences and Spa in Victoria Island, featured presentation of awards to outstanding alumni. Awards were also given to members of the outgoing executive in recognition of their dedication to the growth of the association. In his speech, Ayomide Smith, the outgoing president and first head boy of Atlantic Hall, highlighted various projects executed by the association. Isioma Idigbe-Agba, an alumnae, conducted the oath taking and induction ceremony, and charged the new executives to uphold the values of Atlantic Hall through excellence and integrity. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-631621" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-1024x683.jpeg" alt="" width="900" height="600" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-1024x683.jpeg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-24x16.jpeg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-36x24.jpeg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/WhatsApp-Image-2021-11-22-at-8.24.11-PM-48x32.jpeg 48w, https://f5p3